**Notes on django-orbit**

- App label is `orbit`, middleware is `orbit.middleware.OrbitMiddleware`.
- Has its own migrations (`orbit.0001–0004`); `migrate` picks them up automatically.
- Dashboard renders at `/orbit/` with no additional config — zero-config out of the box.
- Middleware goes at the **end** of `MIDDLEWARE` (after auth/session) so it captures the full authenticated context.
- The `[tool.django] settings_module` key in `pyproject.toml` is informational only (not consumed by Django tooling automatically); `manage.py` and `wsgi.py` each set `DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE` directly.

**Suggested skill changes**

- Add django-orbit to the skill's debug section with: app label `orbit`, middleware `orbit.middleware.OrbitMiddleware`, mount at `path("orbit/", include("orbit.urls"))`, and the note that it applies its own migrations.
- Note that `docker compose up -d --wait --wait-timeout 60` is the right incantation (not `--wait` alone, which exits immediately on older Compose); the `--wait-timeout` guard prevents infinite hang if a healthcheck is misconfigured.
